.TH "vmw_collect_dirty_view_ids" 9 "vmw_collect_dirty_view_ids" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_collect_dirty_view_ids \- Build view id data for a view binding command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmw_collect_dirty_view_ids
.BI "(struct vmw_ctx_binding_state *cbs "  ","
.BI "const struct vmw_ctx_bindinfo *bi "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *dirty "  ","
.BI "u32 max_num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cbs" 12
Pointer to the context's struct vmw_ctx_binding_state
.IP "bi" 12
Pointer to where the binding info array is stored in \fIcbs\fP
.IP "dirty" 12
Bitmap indicating which bindings need to be emitted.
.IP "max_num" 12
Maximum number of entries in the \fIbi\fP array.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Scans the \fIbi\fP array for bindings that need to be emitted and
builds a buffer of view id data.
On output, \fIcbs->bind_cmd_count\fP contains the number of bindings to be
emitted, \fIcbs->bind_first_slot\fP indicates the index of the first emitted
binding, and \fIcbs->bind_cmd_buffer\fP contains the command data.
